files.name: spaceone/api/repository/v1/plugin.proto
files.description: desc: A Plugin is a resource containing data of deployable plugins such as container image and registry URL.

methods.name: register
update
deregister
methods.description:
desc: Deregisters and deletes a specific Plugin. You must specify the `plugin_id` of the Plugin to deregister.
request_example: >-
{
"plugin_id": "plugin-aws-sns-mon-webhook",
"domain_id": "domain-123456789012"
}
response_example: >-
{
"plugin_id": "plugin-aws-sns-mon-webhook",

methods.name: enable
methods.description:

"plugin_id": "plugin-aws-sns-mon-webhook",

methods.description:

methods.name: get_versions
methods.description:
desc: Gets all version data of a specific Plugin from its Repository. The parameter `plugin_id` is used as an identifier of a Plugin to get version data.
request_example: >-
{
"plugin_id": "plugin-aws-sns-mon-webhook",
"domain_id": "domain-123456789012"
}
response_example: >-
{
"total_count": 1,
"results": [
"1.2.2",
"1.2.1.20220429.104002",
"1.2.1.20220422.161421",
"1.2.1.20220411.113807",
"1.2.1"
]
}

"repository_id": "repo-123456789012"
